0#p87763486" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763486</a> </span></div></div><blockquote class="postMessage" id="m87763326">Tell me/g/ why do you guys have autists like <br><a href="#p87763014" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763014</a></blockquote></div></div><div class="postContainer replyContainer" id="pc87763365"><div class="sideArrows" id="sa87763365">&gt;&gt;</div><div id="p87763365" class="post reply"><div class="postInfoM mobile" id="pim87763365">  <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span><br></span><span class="dateTime postNum" data-utc="1658011170">07/16/22(Sat)18:39:30 <a href="#p87763365" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763365');" title="Reply to this post">87763365</a></span></div><div class="postInfo desktop" id="pi87763365"><input type="checkbox" name="87763365" value="delete"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span> </span> <span class="dateTime" data-utc="1658011170">07/16/22(Sat)18:39:30</span> <span class="postNum desktop"><a href="#p87763365" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763365');" title="Reply to this post">87763365</a></span><a href="#" class="postMenuBtn" title="Post menu" data-cmd="post-menu">▶</a><div id="bl_87763365" class="backlink"><span><a href="thread/87761950#p87763447" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763447</a> </span></div></div><blockquote class="postMessage" id="m87763365"><a href="#p87763015" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763015</a><br>I did an x pattern on my 5 year old 1080, works wonderfully.</blockquote></div></div><div class="postContainer replyContainer" id="pc87763408"><div class="sideArrows" id="sa87763408">&gt;&gt;</div><div id="p87763408" class="post reply"><div class="postInfoM mobile" id="pim87763408"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span><br></span><span class="dateTime postNum" data-utc="1658011312">07/16/22(Sat)18:41:52 <a href="#p87763408" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763408');" title="Reply to this post">87763408</a></span></div><div class="postInfo desktop" id="pi87763408"><input type="checkbox" name="87763408" value="delete"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span> </span> <span class="dateTime" data-utc="1658011312">07/16/22(Sat)18:41:52</span> <span class="postNum desktop"><a href="#p87763408" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763408');" title="Reply to this post">87763408</a></span><a href="#" class="postMenuBtn" title="Post menu" data-cmd="post-menu">▶</a></div><blockquote class="postMessage" id="m87763408"><a href="#p87762052" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87762052</a><br><span class="quote">&gt;4 core processors just can't do modern AAA games anymore</span><br>They certainly can. The i3 12100 is an example.<br><br><a href="#p87762176" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87762176</a><br>Then drop out. You don't need a new graphics card<br><br><a href="#p87762330" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87762330</a><br><span class="quote">&gt;buy your 3080 and 3090 NOW or youll regret it..</span><br>If you really need the 24GB of VRAM on a 3090, and you can find one for a steal (we're talking less than $1000 new), probably the best time to buy. The 4090 isn't coming close to that price any time soon. 3080s are neither here nor there; I would wait, but I can see that some people would rather overpay for the performance by a couple of hundred bucks than wait for months for an RTX 40 card.<br><br><a href="#p87762762" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87762762</a><br>Other anon is correct in that the graphics card and SSD go in the slots closest to the CPU. Your motherboard manual will tell you everything you need to know about how lanes are shared and with what. Pic related as an example<br><br><a href="#p87762961" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87762961</a><br><span class="quote">&gt;Will the new PSU standard release at the same time as the new gen? </span><br>Who knows.<br><br>Will it be necessary?<br>No. The Golden Rule of PC building still applies: buy what you need, when you need it, and not before. If you need to pick up a new PSU, and you can get an ATX 3.0 PSU for a reasonable price, great. And if not, don't be a retard and buy a 1500W PSU in an attempt to futureproof yourself out of having to buy an ATX 3.0 PSU later</blockquote></div></div><div class="postContainer replyContainer" id="pc87763420"><div class="sideArrows" id="sa87763420">&gt;&gt;</div><div id="p87763420" class="post reply"><div class="postInfoM mobile" id="pim87763420"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span><br></span><span class="dateTime postNum" data-utc="1658011355">07/16/22(Sat)18:42:35 <a href="#p87763420" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763420');" title="Reply to this post">87763420</a></span></div><div class="postInfo desktop" id="pi87763420"><input type="checkbox" name="87763420" value="delete"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span> </span> <span class="dateTime" data-utc="1658011355">07/16/22(Sat)18:42:35</span> <span class="postNum desktop"><a href="#p87763420" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763420');" title="Reply to this post">87763420</a></span><a href="#" class="postMenuBtn" title="Post menu" data-cmd="post-menu">▶</a><div id="bl_87763420" class="backlink"><span><a href="thread/87761950#p87763486" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763486</a> </span><span><a href="thread/87761950#p87763597" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763597</a> </span></div></div><blockquote class="postMessage" id="m87763420"><a href="#p87763326" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763326</a><br>whenever you have to make a decision for an expensive purchase, you don't want to feel like you made the bad choice so you shill the thing you got to make it seem like you made the right choice<br>it's the same with consoles<br><br>I don't doubt for a second this doesn't also happen with tons of other shit, there's probably people shitposting RIGHT NOW about herman miller vs steelcase</blockquote></div></div><div class="postContainer replyContainer" id="pc87763447"><div class="sideArrows" id="sa87763447">&gt;&gt;</div><div id="p87763447" class="post reply"><div class="postInfoM mobile" id="pim87763447"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span><br></span><span class="dateTime postNum" data-utc="1658011491">07/16/22(Sat)18:44:51 <a href="#p87763447" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763447');" title="Reply to this post">87763447</a></span></div><div class="postInfo desktop" id="pi87763447"><input type="checkbox" name="87763447" value="delete"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span> </span> <span class="dateTime" data-utc="1658011491">07/16/22(Sat)18:44:51</span> <span class="postNum desktop"><a href="#p87763447" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763447');" title="Reply to this post">87763447</a></span><a href="#" class="postMenuBtn" title="Post menu" data-cmd="post-menu">▶</a><div id="bl_87763447" class="backlink"><span><a href="thread/87761950#p87763597" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763597</a> </span></div></div><blockquote class="postMessage" id="m87763447"><a href="/g/thread/87754441#p87762102" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87762102</a><br>lmao you say 20 watts doesn't matter when it's nvidia.<br>But 20 watts increase at idle at the exchange of everything working perfectly makes you sperg.<br><br><a href="/g/thread/87754441#p87763341" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763341</a><br>You can't<br><span class="quote">&gt;get bang for my buck</span><br>gaming for $3000<br>You spend over 100% more than a $1400 build for about 30% better performance in games. That's not bang for your buck.<br>The best you could do is idk overspend needlessly on getting 20TB of SSD storage added to a $1400 build I guess since that'll last you 10+ years and not be going to waste if you can actually use that much storage today.<br><br><a href="#p87763326" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763326</a><br>idk he's mentally ill.<br>He always does that thing where he writes half the post limit about one thing being questionable while saying it's wrong and ignoring all the other things in the same post/video that contradict what he just rambled about.<br>Like he's rambling about muh dx11 drivuh and ignoring that all the games there aren't dx11 and are still +/- 30% off.<br><br><a href="#p87763365" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763365</a><br>Don't do this. Spread it evenly with a credit card or something.</blockquote></div></div><div class="postContainer replyContainer" id="pc87763486"><div class="sideArrows" id="sa87763486">&gt;&gt;</div><div id="p87763486" class="post reply"><div class="postInfoM mobile" id="pim87763486"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span><br></span><span class="dateTime postNum" data-utc="1658011684">07/16/22(Sat)18:48:04 <a href="#p87763486" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763486');" title="Reply to this post">87763486</a></span></div><div class="postInfo desktop" id="pi87763486"><input type="checkbox" name="87763486" value="delete"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span> </span> <span class="dateTime" data-utc="1658011684">07/16/22(Sat)18:48:04</span> <span class="postNum desktop"><a href="#p87763486" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763486');" title="Reply to this post">87763486</a></span><a href="#" class="postMenuBtn" title="Post menu" data-cmd="post-menu">▶</a></div><blockquote class="postMessage" id="m87763486"><a href="#p87763326" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763326</a><br><a href="#p87763420" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763420</a><br><span class="quote">&gt;you don't want to feel like you made the bad choice so you shill the thing you got to make it seem like you made the right choice</span><br>So basically sunk cost fallacy with some buyer's remorse on the side. That explains his mental illness. Fanboyism truly is a disease.</blockquote></div></div><div class="postContainer replyContainer" id="pc87763524"><div class="sideArrows" id="sa87763524">&gt;&gt;</div><div id="p87763524" class="post reply"><div class="postInfoM mobile" id="pim87763524"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span><br></span><span class="dateTime postNum" data-utc="1658011975">07/16/22(Sat)18:52:55 <a href="#p87763524" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763524');" title="Reply to this post">87763524</a></span></div><div class="postInfo desktop" id="pi87763524"><input type="checkbox" name="87763524" value="delete"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span> </span> <span class="dateTime" data-utc="1658011975">07/16/22(Sat)18:52:55</span> <span class="postNum desktop"><a href="#p87763524" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763524');" title="Reply to this post">87763524</a></span><a href="#" class="postMenuBtn" title="Post menu" data-cmd="post-menu">▶</a></div><div class="file" id="f87763524"><div class="fileText" id="fT87763524">File: <a title="D883641D-11D5-4535-9A3E-FE10779C0EA4.jpg" href="//i.4cdn.org/g/1658011975602.jpg" target="_blank">D883641D-11D5-4535-9A3E-F(...).jpg</a> (120 KB, 677x677)</div><a class="fileThumb" href="//i.4cdn.org/g/1658011975602.jpg" target="_blank"><img src="//i.4cdn.org/g/1658011975602s.jpg" alt="120 KB" data-md5="AjFIXCLHqeXZAF0oV0azfw==" style="height: 125px; width: 125px;" loading="lazy"><div data-tip="" data-tip-cb="mShowFull" class="mFileInfo mobile">120 KB JPG</div></a></div><blockquote class="postMessage" id="m87763524"><a href="#p87762330" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87762330</a><br><span class="quote">&gt;panic buy</span><br>what are you, a woman?</blockquote></div></div><div class="postContainer replyContainer" id="pc87763542"><div class="sideArrows" id="sa87763542">&gt;&gt;</div><div id="p87763542" class="post reply"><div class="postInfoM mobile" id="pim87763542"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span><br></span><span class="dateTime postNum" data-utc="1658012056">07/16/22(Sat)18:54:16 <a href="#p87763542" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763542');" title="Reply to this post">87763542</a></span></div><div class="postInfo desktop" id="pi87763542"><input type="checkbox" name="87763542" value="delete"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span> </span> <span class="dateTime" data-utc="1658012056">07/16/22(Sat)18:54:16</span> <span class="postNum desktop"><a href="#p87763542" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763542');" title="Reply to this post">87763542</a></span><a href="#" class="postMenuBtn" title="Post menu" data-cmd="post-menu">▶</a><div id="bl_87763542" class="backlink"><span><a href="thread/87761950#p87763583" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763583</a> </span></div></div><blockquote class="postMessage" id="m87763542"><a href="#p87761950" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87761950 (OP)</a><br>i want to get 4x8gb ram modules (specifically the non-rgb corsair vengeance lpx ones)<br>problem is, i can't find a local store that sells 4 modules together, just 2x8gb ones. and i don't want to order online.<br>so, if i buy 2 of these 2x8gb modules, will that be ok?</blockquote></div></div><div class="postContainer replyContainer" id="pc87763583"><div class="sideArrows" id="sa87763583">&gt;&gt;</div><div id="p87763583" class="post reply"><div class="postInfoM mobile" id="pim87763583"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span><br></span><span class="dateTime postNum" data-utc="1658012315">07/16/22(Sat)18:58:35 <a href="#p87763583" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763583');" title="Reply to this post">87763583</a></span></div><div class="postInfo desktop" id="pi87763583"><input type="checkbox" name="87763583" value="delete"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span> </span> <span class="dateTime" data-utc="1658012315">07/16/22(Sat)18:58:35</span> <span class="postNum desktop"><a href="#p87763583" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763583');" title="Reply to this post">87763583</a></span><a href="#" class="postMenuBtn" title="Post menu" data-cmd="post-menu">▶</a><div id="bl_87763583" class="backlink"><span><a href="thread/87761950#p87763616" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763616</a> </span></div></div><blockquote class="postMessage" id="m87763583"><a href="#p87763542" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763542</a><br>Probably.<br>You can check if they're the same with thaiphoon burner and return them otherwise.</blockquote></div></div><div class="postContainer replyContainer" id="pc87763597"><div class="sideArrows" id="sa87763597">&gt;&gt;</div><div id="p87763597" class="post reply"><div class="postInfoM mobile" id="pim87763597"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span><br></span><span class="dateTime postNum" data-utc="1658012374">07/16/22(Sat)18:59:34 <a href="#p87763597" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763597');" title="Reply to this post">87763597</a></span></div><div class="postInfo desktop" id="pi87763597"><input type="checkbox" name="87763597" value="delete"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span> </span> <span class="dateTime" data-utc="1658012374">07/16/22(Sat)18:59:34</span> <span class="postNum desktop"><a href="#p87763597" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763597');" title="Reply to this post">87763597</a></span><a href="#" class="postMenuBtn" title="Post menu" data-cmd="post-menu">▶</a><div id="bl_87763597" class="backlink"><span><a href="thread/87761950#p87764245" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87764245</a> </span><span><a href="thread/87761950#p87769952" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87769952</a> </span></div></div><blockquote class="postMessage" id="m87763597"><a href="#p87762986" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87762986</a><br>As long as the GPU is within spec, temperature doesn't matter for the health of the card. Generally speaking the card will throttle itself before any harm is done, and the main wear on cards comes from power cycling (and therefore thermal expansion and contraction) rather than sustained load. Temps come into play if the card is having to limit its performance, or if the card is excessively loud, and those two things often go hand in hand. Be aware than you can very easily kill your GPU if you don't correctly repaste and remount the cooler, and of course you have to make sure that any thermal pads are replaced or conserved as well. My advice would be to deshroud and clean the heatsink as thoroughly as possible to try to make the card cooler and quieter (and perhaps better performing).<br><br><a href="#p87763420" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763420</a><br>The anon's original question was about a future purchase. I can tell you from experience that my R5 2600 + RX 470 was often crippled by Radeon's DX11 CPU overhead, so I'm offering him advice about how to avoid the same problems that aggravated me.<br><br><a href="#p87763447" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763447</a><br><span class="quote">&gt;you say 20 watts doesn't matter when it's nvidia.</span><br>At idle, that's a big deal, an extra 100%. At load, 20W is irrelevant. Apples to oranges, kiddo<br><br><span class="quote">&gt;and ignoring that all the games there aren't dx11 and are still +/- 30% off.</span><br>You can definitely hit CPU limits in DX12 games, but generally you don't hit them at or below 60FPS like when Radeon gets crippled by its DX11 driver. DX12 games are only single core sensitive at a relatively high FPS, at least from what I've seen.<br><br><span class="deadlink">&gt;&gt;87763448</span><br><span class="quote">&gt;some buyer's remorse on the side</span><br>Yeah, like when I owned an R9 280X and an RX 470. This is /g/, and these are technical discussion. Don't be mad when you can't keep up</blockquote></div></div><div class="postContainer replyContainer" id="pc87763616"><div class="sideArrows" id="sa87763616">&gt;&gt;</div><div id="p87763616" class="post reply"><div class="postInfoM mobile" id="pim87763616"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span><br></span><span class="dateTime postNum" data-utc="1658012514">07/16/22(Sat)19:01:54 <a href="#p87763616" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763616');" title="Reply to this post">87763616</a></span></div><div class="postInfo desktop" id="pi87763616"><input type="checkbox" name="87763616" value="delete"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span> </span> <span class="dateTime" data-utc="1658012514">07/16/22(Sat)19:01:54</span> <span class="postNum desktop"><a href="#p87763616" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763616');" title="Reply to this post">87763616</a></span><a href="#" class="postMenuBtn" title="Post menu" data-cmd="post-menu">▶</a><div id="bl_87763616" class="backlink"><span><a href="thread/87761950#p87763679" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763679</a> </span></div></div><blockquote class="postMessage" id="m87763616"><a href="#p87763583" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763583</a><br>"probably" doesn't sound good...<br>i can't be bothered with returning stuff so i might actually have to order online.</blockquote></div></div><div class="postContainer replyContainer" id="pc87763679"><div class="sideArrows" id="sa87763679">&gt;&gt;</div><div id="p87763679" class="post reply"><div class="postInfoM mobile" id="pim87763679"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span><br></span><span class="dateTime postNum" data-utc="1658012856">07/16/22(Sat)19:07:36 <a href="#p87763679" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763679');" title="Reply to this post">87763679</a></span></div><div class="postInfo desktop" id="pi87763679"><input type="checkbox" name="87763679" value="delete"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span> </span> <span class="dateTime" data-utc="1658012856">07/16/22(Sat)19:07:36</span> <span class="postNum desktop"><a href="#p87763679" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763679');" title="Reply to this post">87763679</a></span><a href="#" class="postMenuBtn" title="Post menu" data-cmd="post-menu">▶</a></div><blockquote class="postMessage" id="m87763679"><a href="#p87763616" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763616</a><br>Well if they're from the same batch that the store bought at the same time it's like 99%.<br>These companies do switch chips without rebranding if they meet the spec.<br>4x8 kits exist to be 100% sure.</blockquote></div></div><div class="postContainer replyContainer" id="pc87763688"><div class="sideArrows" id="sa87763688">&gt;&gt;</div><div id="p87763688" class="post reply"><div class="postInfoM mobile" id="pim87763688"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span><br></span><span class="dateTime postNum" data-utc="1658012916">07/16/22(Sat)19:08:36 <a href="#p87763688" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763688');" title="Reply to this post">87763688</a></span></div><div class="postInfo desktop" id="pi87763688"><input type="checkbox" name="87763688" value="delete"> <span class="nameBlock"><span class="name">Anonymous</span> </span> <span class="dateTime" data-utc="1658012916">07/16/22(Sat)19:08:36</span> <span class="postNum desktop"><a href="#p87763688" title="Link to this post">No.</a><a href="javascript:quote('87763688');" title="Reply to this post">87763688</a></span><a href="#" class="postMenuBtn" title="Post menu" data-cmd="post-menu">▶</a><div id="bl_87763688" class="backlink"><span><a href="thread/87761950#p87763804" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763804</a> </span><span><a href="thread/87761950#p87763819" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763819</a> </span><span><a href="thread/87761950#p87763924" class="quotelink">&gt;&gt;87763924</a> </span><span><a href="thread/8